# VibeWarden Security Sidecar — AI Agent Instructions

## Overview

This application runs behind **VibeWarden**, a security sidecar process.
VibeWarden listens on port 8080 and proxies requests to this app on
port {{ .UpstreamPort }} after applying security controls.

Do not implement security features that VibeWarden already provides.
{{ if .AuthEnabled }}
## Authentication

VibeWarden handles all authentication via Ory Kratos. Do not write login flows,
session management, or auth middleware in application code.

Authenticated requests carry these headers:

- `X-User-Id` — unique identifier for the authenticated user
- `X-User-Email` — user's email address
- `X-User-Verified` — `"true"` when the email address has been verified

To expose a path without authentication, add it to `vibewarden.yaml`:

```yaml
auth:
  public_paths:
    - "/api/public"
    - "/webhooks/stripe"
```
{{ end }}
{{ if .RateLimitEnabled }}
## Rate Limiting

VibeWarden enforces {{ .RateLimitRPS }} requests/second per client IP.
Do not add rate limiting to application code.

Clients that exceed the limit receive `429 Too Many Requests` before reaching the app.
{{ end }}
{{ if .TLSEnabled }}
## TLS

TLS is terminated by VibeWarden. The application receives plain HTTP on
port {{ .UpstreamPort }}. Do not configure TLS in the app.
{{ end }}
## Security Headers

VibeWarden automatically sets:

- `Strict-Transport-Security`
- `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`
- `X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN`
- `Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'`
- `Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin`

Do not set these headers in application code.

## Special Endpoints

Served by VibeWarden (not the app):

- `GET /_vibewarden/health` — JSON health status, use as liveness probe
{{ if .AdminEnabled }}- `/_vibewarden/admin/*` — admin operations, requires `X-Admin-Key` header{{ end }}

## Configuration

VibeWarden is configured in `vibewarden.yaml`. To change security settings:

1. Edit `vibewarden.yaml`
2. Restart VibeWarden (`docker compose restart vibewarden`)

Full documentation: https://vibewarden.dev/docs/config
